   "source": [
    "# Calculate statistics for functional data attributes\n",
    "\n",
    "Calculate statistical data, such as mean tensile response curves and confidence intervals, from functional data attributes in test records. Import the roll-up data into Granta MI."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Get test data from Granta MI\n",
    "\n",
    "Connect to Granta MI and specify a database and tables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:04.644841Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:04.642830Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:06.356032Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:06.357030Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from GRANTA_MIScriptingToolkit import granta as mpy\n",
    "\n",
    "s = mpy.Session('localhost', autologon=True)\n",
    "db = s.get_db('MI Training')\n",
    "test_table = db.get_table('Tensile Test Data')\n",
    "statistics_table = db.get_table('Tensile Statistical Data')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Records in these tables are organised by test temperature, so we can fetch all the temperature folders in *Tensile Test Data* and their children. \n",
    "\n",
    "Use `table.bulk_fetch()` to efficiently populate the attributes for each test record."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:06.361031Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:06.361031Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.147992Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.148991Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "material_record = test_table.search_for_records_by_name('Plate')[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "temperature_records = {round(rec.children[0].attributes['Test Temperature'].points[0], 1): rec\n",
    "                       for rec in material_record.children}\n",
    "test_records = [temperature.children for temperature in temperature_records.values()]\n",
    "\n",
    "test_table.bulk_fetch([test for tests in test_records for test in tests],\n",
    "                      [test_table.attributes['Tensile Response (11 axis)'],\n",
    "                       test_table.attributes['Specimen ID'],\n",
    "                       test_table.attributes['Test Temperature']])\n",
    "temperature_unit = test_table.attributes['Test Temperature'].unit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create a `pandas` DataFrame and populate it with data from the functional attribute *Tensile Response (11 axis)*, as well as *Specimen ID* and *Test Temperature*. \n",
    "\n",
    "To produce a usable DataFrame, the functional data must:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Have the headers removed\n",
    "2. Be converted from a range into a single value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.153993Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.152990Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.664754Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.664754Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "df_response = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "for group in test_records:\n",
    "    for record in group:\n",
    "        response_attr = record.attributes['Tensile Response (11 axis)']\n",
    "        specimen_id = record.attributes['Specimen ID'].value\n",
    "        test_temperature = record.attributes['Test Temperature'].points[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        df_functional_data = pd.DataFrame(response_attr.data[1:], columns=response_attr.data[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "        df_current = pd.concat([\n",
    "            df_functional_data['Strain [% strain]'],\n",
    "            df_functional_data[['Y min (Tensile Response (11 axis) [MPa])',\n",
    "                                'Y max (Tensile Response (11 axis) [MPa])']]\n",
    "                .mean(axis=1)\n",
    "                .rename('Tensile Response (11 axis) [MPa]')],\n",
    "            axis=1)\n",
    "        df_current['Specimen ID'] = specimen_id\n",
    "        df_current['Test Temperature [{0}]'.format(temperature_unit)] = round(test_temperature, 1)\n",
    "        df_response = pd.concat([df_response, df_current])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Process the data and calculate statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "For easier plotting, interpolate each series onto the union of all the parameter values (`pandas` uses the strain parameter as an index for the union). Any `NaN` inside the populated area for this column is interpolated by the `interpolate()` method with `limit_area='inside'`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Group the data by *Test Temperature*, then use `scipy` to calculate the 95% confidence intervals by passing the count, mean and standard deviation of the grouped data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.668751Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:13.667751Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:15.978760Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:15.978760Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import scipy.stats as st\n",
    "df_interpolated = df_response.pivot(index='Strain [% strain]',\n",
    "                                    values='Tensile Response (11 axis) [MPa]',\n",
    "                                    columns=['Specimen ID', 'Test Temperature [K]']) \\\n",
    "    .interpolate(method='index', limit_direction='both', limit_area='inside')\n",
    "\n",
    "grouped_by = df_interpolated.groupby(level='Test Temperature [K]', axis=1)\n",
    "confidence_intervals = st.t.interval(0.95, grouped_by.count(), loc=grouped_by.mean(), scale=grouped_by.std())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Convert the transformed data into an aggregate DataFrame for plotting and import, taking the minimum, maximum, confidence intervals and mean at each strain value and temperature."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:15.992761Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:15.991761Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:16.176774Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:16.177775Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_all_plots = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "\n",
    "for temperature_index, temperature in enumerate(grouped_by.groups):\n",
    "    # Convert the confidence intervals into a DataFrame\n",
    "    df_cis = pd.DataFrame(data=zip(*[[row[temperature_index] for row in confidence_intervals[0]],\n",
    "                                     [row[temperature_index] for row in confidence_intervals[1]]]),\n",
    "                          index=df_interpolated.index).rename(columns={0: 'lower_ci', 1: 'upper_ci'})\n",
    "    # Combine with the other derived quantities\n",
    "    df_plot = pd.concat([grouped_by.mean()[temperature].rename('mean'),\n",
    "                         grouped_by.min()[temperature].rename('min'),\n",
    "                         grouped_by.max()[temperature].rename('max'),\n",
    "                         df_cis], axis=1).dropna()\n",
    "    # Polish up the DataFrame for aggregation\n",
    "    df_plot['temperature'] = temperature\n",
    "    df_plot = df_plot.rename_axis('strain')\n",
    "    df_all_plots = pd.concat([df_all_plots, df_plot.reset_index()])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot the aggregated data using `matplotlib`, creating a grid of subplots with identical (shared) axes to easily compare the tensile response at different temperatures."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:16.183774Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:16.183774Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.276766Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.277767Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1125x1750 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 125\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(9, 14), sharex='all', sharey='all')\n",
    "\n",
    "for plot_index, temperature in enumerate(grouped_by.groups):\n",
    "    ax = axs[plot_index // 2][plot_index % 2]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Get the rows corresponding to the current temperature\n",
    "    df_plot = df_all_plots.loc[df_all_plots['temperature'] == temperature]\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.plot(df_plot['strain'], df_plot['mean'], label='Mean')\n",
    "    ax.fill_between(df_plot['strain'],\n",
    "                    df_plot['lower_ci'],\n",
    "                    df_plot['upper_ci'],\n",
    "                    label='95% Confidence Interval',\n",
    "                    hatch='\\\\', facecolor='C0', edgecolor='C0', alpha=0.25)\n",
    "    ax.fill_between(df_plot['strain'],\n",
    "                    df_plot['min'],\n",
    "                    df_plot['max'],\n",
    "                    label='Observed range', hatch='.', facecolor='none', edgecolor='C3')\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_title(\"Tensile response at {0} {1}\".format(round(temperature, 0), temperature_unit))\n",
    "    ax.grid('major')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.setp(axs[-1, :], xlabel='Strain / % strain')\n",
    "plt.setp(axs[:, 0], ylabel='Tensile Response (11 axis) / MPa')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import roll-up data into Granta MI\n",
    "\n",
    "Define two helper functions: one that resamples a DataFrame linearly based on a target column's values, and one that appends a series of range values to a `FloatFunctionalAttributeValue`, skipping any `NaN` values.\n",
    "\n",
    "(Although `pandas` has a built-in `resample()` function, it only operates on time-series data.)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.282767Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.282767Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.292771Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.292771Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def subsample_dataframe(df, x_axis, n_samples):\n",
    "    new_index = np.linspace(df[x_axis].min(), df[x_axis].max(), n_samples)\n",
    "    df.index = df[x_axis]\n",
    "    df_subsampled = df.reindex(df.index.union(new_index)).interpolate('index').reindex(index=new_index)\n",
    "    df_subsampled.index = range(n_samples)\n",
    "    return df_subsampled\n",
    "\n",
    "def append_series(functional_attribute, x_data, y_low_data, y_high_data=None, data_type=None):\n",
    "    if y_high_data is None:\n",
    "        y_high_data = y_low_data\n",
    "    for x, y_low, y_high in zip(x_data, y_low_data, y_high_data):\n",
    "        if pd.isna(y_low) or pd.isna(y_high):\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        functional_attribute.data.append([y_low, y_high, x, data_type, False])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Import the roll-up data into Granta MI. Use `path_from()` to create a folder path with the new statistical data record at the end node, and populate the *Test Temperature* and *Tensile Response Analysis (11 axis)* attributes using the helper functions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Write the new record to Granta MI using `Session.update()`, then link the newly-created attribute to the relevant test results. Finally, write the new links to Granta MI using `Session.update_links()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.299770Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-07-15T10:13:17.299770Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-07-15T10:13:46.071487Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-07-15T10:13:46.072486Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "t_statistics = db.get_table('Tensile Statistical Data')\n",
    "timestamp = datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n",
    "for plot_index, temperature in enumerate(grouped_by.groups):\n",
    "    # Create a record to store the imported data\n",
    "    rec = t_statistics.path_from(starting_node=None, tree_path=['Data Analytics', timestamp],\n",
    "                                 end_node='Functional Rollup ({0} {1})'.format(round(temperature, 0), temperature_unit),\n",
    "                                 color='Olive')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    temp_attribute = rec.attributes['Test Temperature']\n",
    "    temp_attribute.points = [temperature]\n",
    "    temp_attribute.unit = temperature_unit\n",
    "\n",
    "    func_attr = rec.attributes['Tensile Response Analysis (11 axis)']\n",
    "    func_attr.unit = 'MPa'\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Get the rows corresponding to the current temperature\n",
    "    df_current = df_all_plots.loc[df_all_plots['temperature'] == temperature]\n",
    "\n",
    "    df_current = subsample_dataframe(df_current, 'strain', 101)\n",
    "    append_series(func_attr, df_current['strain'], df_current['mean'], data_type='Mean')\n",
    "    append_series(func_attr, df_current['strain'], df_current['lower_ci'], df_current['upper_ci'], data_type='95% Confidence Interval')\n",
    "    append_series(func_attr, df_current['strain'], df_current['min'], df_current['max'], data_type='Range')\n",
    "\n",
    "    rec.set_attributes([temp_attribute, func_attr])\n",
    "    rec = s.update([rec])[0]\n",
    "    rec.set_links('Tensile Test Data', temperature_records[temperature].children)\n",
    "    s.update_links([rec])\n"
   ]
  },
